|GKO================================================================
                   |WKOGarou Guild : Pack Creation
|GKO================================================================
|YKOTo create a pack, you must be level 20 or higher. Additionally,
the pack must be approved by the Garou Council. The Council
is run by the current Garou pack leadership, with each pack 
getting one vote on the issue of new pack creation.

The first step in creating a new pack is to submit a request
using the the |YKB'requestpack' |YKOcommand. As part of your request,
you will have to enter a description of your pack's philosophy.
Think carefully on this issue. This is the only place you get
to enter your pack's philosophy. After the pack is approved and
created, you cannot change its philosophy. Your only option
would be to disband your pack and request/create a completely
new one.

Once a request has been completed, it is sent to the Council.
The Council has 3 weeks to vote on the issue. At the end of
the 3 weeks, the pack is automatically approved if it has not
received 4 or more 'no' votes. If at any time during those
3 weeks it becomes impossible to get 4 'no' votes, the pack
is automatically approved. For example, if there are only 4
packs and one has already voted 'yes', then it is impossible
to get 4 'no' votes and the request would immediately be
approved.

Only packs which have atleast 2 members, one being a leader,
keeper, or shaman, login within the past 45 days are eligible
to vote. Ineligible packs can become eligible if enough members
login before the deadline. Ineligible packs do not count as
pending votes; thus if there are less than 4 active packs,
any request for a new pack would automatically be approved
since there would be no way to receive 4 eligible 'no' votes.
The same holds true if there is simply less than 4 actual
packs, active or not. 

Once a request has been approved or rejected, a mudmail
confirmation of the decision is automatically sent to the
prospective leader. If the pack is approved, the Garou will
now be able to create his/her pack by using the 'createpack'
command.
